      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA benchmark pump hemolysis validation",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against FDA benchmark experimental data across 5 operating conditions. Mean relative error in normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) was 8.3%, within the 15% acceptance band. Turbulence model performance in low-shear near-wall regions was identified as a limitation affecting predicted shear stress distributions at off-design flow rates; edge cases at the lowest flow condition (2.5 L/min, 2500 RPM) were not fully covered by the experimental dataset. The assessment team notes this limitation but considers the overall risk acceptable."
    },
